How can we detect:
1. Bluetooth device connections
2. Bluetooth file transfers (OBEX protocol)
3. Unusual usage of fsquirt.exe (Windows Bluetooth File Transfer Wizard)
4. Execution of Bluetooth-related commands/utilities (like bluetoothctl, btmon in Linux)

Common Registry Paths Modified During Bluetooth Events

Purpose	Registry Path

Bluetooth device pairing	HKLM\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\BTHPORT\Parameters\Devices\
Bluetooth device services	HKLM\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\BthEnum\
Installed Bluetooth driver	HKLM\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\BTHUSB\
Device metadata	HKLM\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Enum\BTHENUM\
Paired devices (user level)	HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Bluetooth\DeviceCache\
Bluetooth settings	HKLM\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Bluetooth or HKCU\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Bluetooth

